The following ciphertext was generated using a 40 x 40 Cardano
grille. The grille has somewhat fewer holes than might be expected.
A normal grille would have (40*40)/4 holes. This has about (40*40)/6
holes. This means that a proportion of the text below is filler 
characters. 

There is no prize for this, and in about a week, I'll post the
solution in the form of a postscript file which draws the grille
on one page and the ciphertext on another. Photocopying the
grille onto clear plastic film will give you the decoder!

This all arose from trying to make a cipher that was *reasonably*
secure, but was *very* easy to decode. This cipher meets these 
requirements - the decoding is certainly easy -- you just line up
the grille over the text and read off the solution. Rotate the grille
and read off the next bit, etc, etc. In operational use, the text would
be transported either in a letter or by fax and would be sent
already in the grid. [Slight worries about dimensional stability of fax
machines].

The text below is in the 40x40 array.

Good Luck!

Philip
